'''Alberto Abdiel Quintero Medina''' (born 18 December 1987) is a Panamanian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[C.D. Plaza Amador]] and the [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]] as a [[winger (association football)|winger]].

==Club career==
===Early years and Spain===
Nicknamed ''Negrito'', Quintero was born in [[Panama City]]. After beginning in his country with [[Club Deportivo Universitario|Chorrillo F.C.]] he moved to Spain in the summer of 2008, playing amateur football with [[Torrellano CF]] in [[Elche]].<ref>[http://impresa.prensa.com/deportes/jugadores-Chorrillo-van-Espana_0_2339766681.html Tres jugadores del Chorrillo van a España (Three Chorrillo players go to Spain)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117034352/http://impresa.prensa.com/deportes/jugadores-Chorrillo-van-Espana_0_2339766681.html|date=17 November 2015}}; La Prensa, 17 July 2008 {{in lang|es}}</ref> He became a key player for the team,<ref>{{Cite news |last=Loves |first=M. |date=24 November 2008 |title=Quintero lidera al Torrellano |trans-title=Quintero leads Torrellano |url=https://www.informacion.es/deportes/2008/11/24/quintero-lidera-torrellano-7418470.html |access-date=11 November 2024 |work=Información |language=Spanish}}</ref> which achieved promotion to the [[Tercera División|Spanish Third Division]].

After a sole season, Quintero joined [[FC Cartagena]],<ref>[http://laestrella.com.pa/deportes/mas-deportes/alberto-quintero-promete-10-goles/23749037 Alberto Quintero promete 10 goles (Alberto Quintero promises 10 goals)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171029012456/http://laestrella.com.pa/deportes/mas-deportes/alberto-quintero-promete-10-goles/23749037|date=29 October 2017}}; La Estrella, 2 September 2009 {{in lang|es}}</ref> three levels above his previous and just [[2008–09 Segunda División B|returned]] to [[Segunda División]]. Since he had arrived in Spain with a tourist visa, which expired after three months, he resided illegally in the country for almost a year before regularizing his residence status with the help of Cartagena.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Vera |first=José A. |date=30 September 2009 |title=Quintero: de sin papeles hasta el Ruiz de Lopera |trans-title=Quintero: from being without papers to the Ruiz de Lopera |url=https://as.com/futbol/2009/09/30/mas_futbol/1254292080_850215.html |access-date=11 November 2024 |work=[[Diario AS|AS]] |language=Spanish}}</ref> He struggled tremendously while adjusting to his new team, namely in an incident at [[Real Betis]] on 27 September 2009 (0–0 draw) where he was subjected to constant racist abuse by the opposing fans.<ref>[http://www.aldiatx.com/sharedcontent/APStories/stories/D9B0DG200.html Arbitro paró partido en España por insultos racistas a panameño (Referee halted match in Spain for racist insults to Panamanian)] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091002210857/http://www.aldiatx.com/sharedcontent/APStories/stories/D9B0DG200.html|date=2 October 2009}}; Al Día TX, 28 September 2009 {{in lang|es}}</ref> His debut in the competition took place on 5 September, coming on as a late [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in a 2–0 home win against [[Rayo Vallecano]].<ref>[http://www.marca.com/2009/09/05/futbol/2adivision/1252175338.html Toché y Tato ponen en lo más alto al Cartagena (Toché and Tato put Cartagena on top of top)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140606234514/http://www.marca.com/2009/09/05/futbol/2adivision/1252175338.html|date=6 June 2014}}; [[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]], 5 September 2009 {{in lang|es}}</ref>

In 2010, he signed with [[Ontinyent CF]] of the [[Segunda División B]],<ref>[http://impresa.prensa.com/deportes/sueno-ascender-OntinyentQuintero_0_2944205608.html ‘Mi sueño es ascender con Ontinyent’, Quintero ('I dream of promoting with Ontinyent', Quintero)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304064134/http://impresa.prensa.com/deportes/sueno-ascender-OntinyentQuintero_0_2944205608.html|date=4 March 2016}}; La Prensa, 1 October 2010 {{in lang|es}}</ref> for the [[2010–11 Segunda División B|2010-11 season]]. In 2011, after one season with Ontinyent, Quintero returned to his country and Chorrillo.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.diaadia.com.pa/deportes-old/negrito-jugara-con-chorrillo-en-la-lpf-514056 |title="Negrito" jugará con Chorrillo en la LPF |trans-title="Little Black" will play with Chorrillo in PFL |publisher=Día a Día |language=es |date=30 August 2011 |access-date=16 February 2023 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230216020031/https://www.diaadia.com.pa/deportes-old/negrito-jugara-con-chorrillo-en-la-lpf-514056 |archive-date=16 February 2023}}</ref>

===Mexico===
Following a successful campaign for Panama at the [[2013 CONCACAF Gold Cup]], Quintero caught the attention of [[C.F. Pachuca]], who was due to sign him in August 2013.<ref>[http://www.elsiglo.com/mensual/2013/08/02/contenido/679370.asp Un ‘Negrito’ en Pachuca (A 'Little Black' in Pachuca)] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130808063348/http://www.elsiglo.com/mensual/2013/08/02/contenido/679370.asp|date=8 August 2013}}; El Siglo, 2 August 2013 {{in lang|es}}</ref> Nothing came of it, but he moved to another club in Mexico, [[Ascenso MX]]'s [[Lobos BUAP]].<ref>[http://impresa.prensa.com/deportes/Negrito-Quintero-Mexico_0_3722627926.html Negrito Quintero, a México (Little Black Quintero, to Mexico)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161104081241/http://impresa.prensa.com/deportes/Negrito-Quintero-Mexico_0_3722627926.html|date=4 November 2016}}; La Prensa, 4 August 2013 {{in lang|es}}</ref>

After one season at BUAP, Quintero was signed by [[Venados F.C.|C.F. Mérida]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rpctv.com/deportes/futbol/Alberto-Negrito-Quintero-CF-Merida_0_653335642.html |title=Alberto "Negrito" Quintero entrena con el CF Mérida, su nuevo equipo |trans-title=Alberto "Little Black" Quintero trains with CF Mérida, his new team |publisher=[[RPC (Panama)|RPC]] |language=es |date=18 December 2013 |access-date=16 February 2023 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230216020031/https://www.rpctv.com/deportes/futbol/Alberto-Negrito-Quintero-CF-Merida_0_653335642.html |archive-date=16 February 2023}}</ref> and then moved to [[Mineros de Zacatecas]],<ref>[http://www.imagenzac.com.mx/nota/reforzara-nalberto-quintero-na-los-mine-19-22-09-5d Reforzará Alberto Quintero a los Mineros (Alberto Quintero to strengthen Mineros)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305165511/http://www.imagenzac.com.mx/nota/reforzara-nalberto-quintero-na-los-mine-19-22-09-5d|date=5 March 2016}}; Zacatecas en Imagen, 10 June 2014 {{in lang|es}}</ref> followed by a return to BUAP in January 2015.<ref>[http://www.cableondasports.com/futbol/nacional/legionarios-cos/roberto-nurse-y-alberto-quintero-tendran-nuevos-equipos Roberto Nurse y Alberto Quintero tendrán nuevos equipos (Roberto Nurse and Alberto Quintero will have new teams)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170315002735/http://www.cableondasports.com/futbol/nacional/legionarios-cos/roberto-nurse-y-alberto-quintero-tendran-nuevos-equipos|date=15 March 2017}}; Cable Onda Sports, 19 December 2014 {{in lang|es}}</ref> Eleven months later, he was loaned to [[San Jose Earthquakes]] of [[Major League Soccer]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/san-jose-earthquakes-acquire-panamanian-midfielder-alberto-quintero-loan |title=San Jose Earthquakes acquire Panamanian midfielder Alberto Quintero on loan |publisher=[[Major League Soccer]] |date=24 February 2016 |access-date=16 June 2022 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220616175736/https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/san-jose-earthquakes-acquire-panamanian-midfielder-alberto-quintero-loan |archive-date=16 June 2022}}</ref> scoring two of their three goals on 12 May in the 3–1 home victory over [[Houston Dynamo FC]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://eu.usatoday.com/story/sports/mls/2016/05/12/quintero-has-2-goals-and-an-assist-in-earthquakes-3-1-win/84268732/ |title=Quintero has 2 goals and an assist in Earthquakes' 3–1 win |publisher=[[USA Today]] |date=12 May 2016 |access-date=16 June 2022}}</ref>

Quintero joined [[Peruvian Primera División]] side [[Club Universitario de Deportes]] on 30 January 2017.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://elcomercio.pe/deporte-total/futbol-peruano/universitario-anuncio-fichaje-panameno-alberto-quintero-161866-noticia/ |title=Universitario anunció el fichaje del panameño Alberto Quintero |trans-title=Universitario announced signing of Panama's Alberto Quintero |publisher=[[El Comercio (Peru)|El Comercio]] |language=es |date=30 January 2017 |access-date=16 June 2022 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220616175736/https://elcomercio.pe/deporte-total/futbol-peruano/universitario-anuncio-fichaje-panameno-alberto-quintero-161866-noticia/ |archive-date=16 June 2022}}</ref> He was initially criticized by the team's supporters for not being fit for playing; however, after the arrival of manager [[Pedro Troglio]], Quintero became one of the club's players who stood out the most, scoring a career-best 13 goals in his [[2017 Torneo Descentralizado|first season]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://rpp.pe/futbol/descentralizado/alberto-quintero-destaco-a-los-hinchas-de-universitario-en-su-recuperacion-noticia-1144897 |title=Alberto Quintero destacó a los hinchas de Universitario en su recuperación |trans-title=Alberto Quintero highlighted Universitario fans in his recovery |publisher=[[Radio Programas del Perú]] |language=es |date=21 August 2018 |access-date=16 June 2022 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220616175715/https://rpp.pe/futbol/descentralizado/alberto-quintero-destaco-a-los-hinchas-de-universitario-en-su-recuperacion-noticia-1144897 |archive-date=16 June 2022}}</ref>

==International career==
Quintero was part of the [[Panama national under-20 football team|Panama]] squad that participated in the [[2007 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] in Canada.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.elgrafico.com.ar/articulo/1003/207/argentina-caminando |title=Argentina, caminando |trans-title=Argentina, walking |publisher=[[El Gráfico (Argentina)|El Gráfico]] |language=es |date=3 July 2007 |access-date=16 June 2022 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230418065502/https://www.elgrafico.com.ar/articulo/1003/207/argentina-caminando |archive-date=18 April 2023}}</ref> He made his [[Panama national football team|full]] debut that same year, in a [[Exhibition game|friendly]] against [[Guatemala national football team|Guatemala]].<ref>[https://www.rsssf.org/miscellaneous/panama-recintlp.html Panama – Record International Players] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150417132750/http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/panama-recintlp.html|date=17 April 2015}}; at [[RSSSF]]</ref>

Quintero represented his country in 14 [[FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches,<ref>{{FIFA player|271116}}</ref> and was selected for the [[2013 CONCACAF Gold Cup]], helping the ''Canaleros'' to finish second in the United States. He was also picked for [[2015 CONCACAF Gold Cup|the following edition]], scoring in the group stage opener against [[Haiti national football team|Haiti]] (1–1).<ref>[http://prosoccertalk.nbcsports.com/2015/07/07/panama-1-1-haiti-nazons-dizzying-move-helps-les-grenadiers-to-surprising-draw-video/ Panama 1–1 Haiti: Nazon's dizzying move helps Les Grenadiers to surprising draw (video)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150710135810/http://prosoccertalk.nbcsports.com/2015/07/07/panama-1-1-haiti-nazons-dizzying-move-helps-les-grenadiers-to-surprising-draw-video/|date=10 July 2015}}; [[NBC Sports]], 7 July 2015</ref>

In May 2018, Quintero was named in Panama's final 23-man squad for [[2018 FIFA World Cup|the upcoming edition]] of the [[FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>[http://www.marca.com/claro-mx/futbol/mundial/2018/05/30/5b0ee9e5e2704ee57c8b4621.html Panamá da la lista de los 23 jugadores que irán al Mundial de Rusia 2018 (Panamá release list of 23 players who will go to 2018 Russia World Cup)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612143404/http://www.marca.com/claro-mx/futbol/mundial/2018/05/30/5b0ee9e5e2704ee57c8b4621.html|date=12 June 2018}}; Marca, 30 May 2018 {{in lang|es}}</ref> On 6 June, however, he suffered a fractured foot in a [[Exhibition game|friendly]] with [[Norway national football team|Norway]] after a collision with [[Bjørn Johnsen]], thus being ruled out of the tournament and replaced by [[Ricardo Ávila]].<ref>[https://elcomercio.pe/mundial/panama-rusia-2018-alberto-quintero-pierde-mundial-lesion-noticia-525747 Panamá: Alberto Quintero se pierde el Mundial Rusia 2018 por lesión (Panama: Alberto Quintero misses World Cup Russia 2018 due to injury)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612162149/https://elcomercio.pe/mundial/panama-rusia-2018-alberto-quintero-pierde-mundial-lesion-noticia-525747|date=12 June 2018}}; [[El Comercio (Peru)|El Comercio]], 6 June 2018 {{in lang|es}}</ref>

On 5 September 2019, Quintero played his 100th match against [[Bermuda national football team|Bermuda]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://rpp.pe/futbol/futbol-mundial/universitario-de-deportes-ver-gol-alberto-quintero-dio-dos-asistencias-en-el-triunfo-de-panama-por-la-liga-de-naciones-de-la-concacaf-noticia-1218171 |title=¡Se lució! Alberto Quintero dio dos asistencias en el triunfo de Panamá por la Liga de Naciones de la Concacaf |trans-title=He shone! Alberto Quintero assisted twice in Panama win in Concacaf Nations League |publisher=Radio Programas del Perú |language=es |date=5 September 2019 |access-date=8 September 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190916094430/https://rpp.pe/futbol/futbol-mundial/universitario-de-deportes-ver-gol-alberto-quintero-dio-dos-asistencias-en-el-triunfo-de-panama-por-la-liga-de-naciones-de-la-concacaf-noticia-1218171 |archive-date=16 September 2019}}</ref>

